  "title": "ISic001101. Dedication by Pasion Seisurion, son of Dekkios, of Segesta",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-text=\"ἐπὶ\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"\">ἐ̣πὶ</span>  <span data-text=\"ταμία\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"\">ταμία</span>  <span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Λευκίου Καικιλίου\n                    ΛΔευκίου υἱοῦ Μετέλλου\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"praenomen\" data-text=\"Λευκίου\"><span data-text=\"Λευκίου\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"\">Λευκίου</span></span>  <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"nomen\" data-text=\"Καικιλίου\"><span data-text=\"Καικιλίου\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"\">Καικιλίου</span></span>  <br id=\"al2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"ΛΔευκίου\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"ΛΔευκίου\"><span data-text=\"ΛΔευκίου\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"\">&lt;Λ&gt;ευκίου</span></span></span>  <span data-text=\"υἱοῦ\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"\">υἱοῦ</span>  <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"cognomen\" data-text=\"Μετέλλου\"><span data-text=\"Μετέλλου\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"\">Μετέλλου<span dir=\"ltr\">(vac.3)</span></span></span></span>  <br id=\"al3-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Πασίων Δεκκίου Σεισυρίων\n                    Ἐγεσταῖος\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Πασίων\"><span data-text=\"Πασίων\" data-n=\"45\" data-lemma=\"\">Πασίων</span></span>  <span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Δεκκίου\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Δεκκίου\"><span data-text=\"Δεκκίου\" data-n=\"50\" data-lemma=\"\">Δεκκίου</span></span></span>  <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Σεισυρίων\"><span data-text=\"Σεισυρίων\" data-n=\"55\" data-lemma=\"\">Σε̣ισυρίων</span></span>  <br id=\"al4-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span><span data-text=\"Ἐγεσταῖος\" data-n=\"60\" data-lemma=\"\">Ἐγεσταῖος</span></span>  <span data-text=\"χιλιαρχήσας\" data-n=\"65\" data-lemma=\"\">χιλιαρχήσας</span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\">l.2 Λ</p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-text=\"ἐπὶ\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"\">.ΠΙ</span><span data-text=\"ταμία\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"\">ΤΑΜΙΑ</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Λευκίου Καικιλίου\n                    ΛΔευκίου υἱοῦ Μετέλλου\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"praenomen\" data-text=\"Λευκίου\"><span data-text=\"Λευκίου\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"\">ΛΕΥΚΙΟΥ</span></span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"nomen\" data-text=\"Καικιλίου\"><span data-text=\"Καικιλίου\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"\">ΚΑΙΚΙΛΙΟΥ</span></span><br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"ΛΔευκίου\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"ΛΔευκίου\"><span data-text=\"ΛΔευκίου\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"\">ΔΕΥΚΙΟΥ</span></span></span><span data-text=\"υἱοῦ\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"\">ΥΙΟΥ</span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"cognomen\" data-text=\"Μετέλλου\"><span data-text=\"Μετέλλου\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"\">ΜΕΤΕΛΛΟΥ&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><br id=\"al3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Πασίων Δεκκίου Σεισυρίων\n                    Ἐγεσταῖος\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Πασίων\"><span data-text=\"Πασίων\" data-n=\"45\" data-lemma=\"\">ΠΑΣΙΩΝ</span></span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Δεκκίου\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Δεκκίου\"><span data-text=\"Δεκκίου\" data-n=\"50\" data-lemma=\"\">ΔΕΚΚΙΟΥ</span></span></span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Σεισυρίων\"><span data-text=\"Σεισυρίων\" data-n=\"55\" data-lemma=\"\">Σ.ΙΣΥΡΙΩΝ</span></span><br id=\"al4-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span><span data-text=\"Ἐγεσταῖος\" data-n=\"60\" data-lemma=\"\">ΕΓΕΣΤΑΙΟΣ</span></span><span data-text=\"χιλιαρχήσας\" data-n=\"65\" data-lemma=\"\">ΧΙΛΙΑΡΧΗΣΑΣ</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\">l.2 Λ</p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic001101_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo M. Metcalfe\" src=\"ISic001101_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic001101.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo M. Metcalfe\" src=\"ISic001101-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic001101_copya_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo M. Metcalfe\" src=\"ISic001101_copya_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic001101_copya.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo M. Metcalfe\" src=\"ISic001101_copya-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span>  <span>Text from autopsy (Prag)</span>  </span>; </li><li><span class=\"Line 2\">Line.2: <span>The stone reads Δευκίου</span>  </span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag</a></p>  <p>In the quaestorship of Lucius Caecilius Metellus, son of Lucius: Pasion Seisurion, son of Dekkios, Segestan, having served as chiliarch</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>The block is presumably part of a dedication to Venus Erycina, made by a member of the Segestan elite who served as a military commander during the period of the Roman Republican province. It is likely that this was to commemorate his service as the Sicilian commander of the honorific garrison of 200 men stationed at Eryx, described by Diodorus Siculus (4.83.7), as well as Cicero (Verr. 5.124), and for which the 17 Sicilian towns that had remained most loyal to Rome were responsible (see <a href=\"https://www.jstor.org/stable/20430572 \" target=\"_blank\">Prag, JRS 2007</a> pp. 81-82 with references). A similar text can be seen in CIL 10.7258 = <a href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000538\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000538</a>. The name <a href=\"http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?namenoaccents=%CE%A0%CE%91%CE%A3%CE%99%CE%A9%CE%9D\" target=\"_blank\">Pasion</a> is moderately well attested in Sicily as well is in the wider Greek world, whereas Seisurion is assumed to be an indigenous form. The Lucius Caecilius L.f. Metellus in question is normally identified with the son of the Metellus who governed Sicily after Verres, in 70 BC, and who held the quaestorship referred to here in 52 BC, as by Broughton and others (see <a href=\"http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/person/2480\" target=\"_blank\">http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/person/2480</a>). </p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> Gualtherus 1624 258 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388</a>  </li><li> Gualtherus 1624 [1625] 151 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931</a>  </li><li> Franz 1853 5501 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250</a>  </li><li> Kaibel 1890 <a href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">282</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072</a>  </li><li> Hoffmann 1904 5192 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000817\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000817</a>  </li><li> Cagnat 1906 501 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001116\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001116</a>  </li><li> De Vido 1991 974 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001409\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001409</a>  </li><li> De Vido 2003 400 no.14 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002041\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002041</a>  </li><li> Prag 2007 82 n.78 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001667\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001667</a>  </li><li> Ampolo and Erdas 2019 App.5 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001036\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001036</a>  </li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> <p> Types list: <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type1.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type1.3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Κ-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Κ type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Κ-type1.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Κ type1.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Κ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Κ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Κ-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Κ type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Μ-type3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Μ type3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Μ-type3.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Μ type3.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ν-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ν type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ν-type2.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ν type2.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ο-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ο type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Σ-tyoe3.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Σ tyoe3.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Σ-type3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Σ type3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Υ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Υ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Υ-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Υ type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ω-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ω type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ω-type1.4.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ω type1.4</a> </p> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  </div>",
